# Module 7: Multiway Pots

## Learning Objectives
By the end of this module, you will:
- Understand why **multiway pots** dramatically change GTO strategy compared to heads-up.
- Learn key adjustments: tighter ranges, lower frequencies, more nutted betting.
- Master **capping ranges**, reduced bluffing, and defending vs multiple opponents.
- Analyze common multiway spots (e.g., BB vs UTG + BTN).
- Avoid common leaks in multiway scenarios.

Multiway pots (3+ players) are tougher: lower equity realization, capped ranges, less fold equity. GTO shifts defensive.

## Why Multiway Changes Everything
- **Equity Distribution**: Your hand's equity drops (shared among players).
- **Range Capping**: Callers behind cap your range (fewer nuts).
- **Reduced Aggression**: Lower c-bet/barrel freqs (bluffs get called more).
- **Nut Advantage Critical**: Bet only strong/nuts; medium hands check/call.

![Multiway vs Heads-Up Comparison Thumbnail](https://blog.gtowizard.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/gto-wizard-multiway-mechanics-blog-article-thumbnail-image.jpg)
