## Key GTO Adjustments in Multiway
| Aspect                  | Heads-Up SRP/3-Bet                    | Multiway                              |
|-------------------------|---------------------------------------|---------------------------------------|
| **C-Bet Frequency**     | 60-90%                               | 30-60% (nutted only)                 |
| **Bluff:Value Ratio**   | 1:1 to 2:1                           | 1:2+ (fewer bluffs)                  |
| **Check-Raise Freq**    | 10-20%                               | 15-30% (traps with nuts)             |
| **Defending Freq**      | Wide (MDF high)                      | Tighter (cap range)                  |
| **Sizing**              | Small-medium                         | Larger (protect, but selective)      |

![Multiway Range Example](https://blog.gtowizard.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/gto-wizard-multiway-mechanics-image-17.jpg)
*(Source: GTO Wizard – Flop ranges in multiway pots)*

![Multiway Big Bet Opportunities](https://www.poker.pro/wp-content/uploads/multiway-muscle-gto-wizard-b-1024x594.png)
*(Source: PokerPro – Solver insights for multiway betting)*

**Aggressor (IP/OOP)**: C-bet only nuts/draws with backup. Check medium strength.

**Defenders**: Check-raise more (nuts advantage OOP), overfold air.

## Common Multiway Spots
- **BB vs UTG + CO/BTN**: Defend tighter preflop (cap UTG). Postflop: Check most, CR strong.
- **Squeezes**: 3-bet less (multiway harder).
- **Flop Play**: Dry boards → bet top sets+; wet → check nuts to induce.

